      </author>
    </authorgroup>
  </info>

  <part id="usermanual">
    <title>User Manual</title>
    <partintro>
      <para>
        This part gives an introduction into the OpenEngSB project and explains it base usage environment
        and the base concepts, such as Tool Domains, Tool Connectors, OpenEngSB workflows and similar
        important ideas.
        It explains how to install,
        setup and use the OpenEngSB administration interface to implement a tool environment according
        to your needs.
      </para>
      <para>
        The target audience of this part are users and developers of OpenEngSB.
      </para>
    </partintro>
    <xi:include href="user/whatisopenengsb.xml" />
    <xi:include href="user/whenuseopenengsb.xml" />
    <xi:include href="user/gettingstarted.xml" />
    <xi:include href="user/testclient.xml" />
  </part>

  <part id="developerManual">
    <title>Developer Manual</title>
    <partintro>
      <para>
        This part explains how to develop additional OpenEngSB connectors, tools and similar parts. In
        addition it explains the rules and infrastructure according to which the OpenEngSB project is
        developed.
      </para>
      <para>
        The target audience of this part are developers of OpenEngSB.
      </para>
    </partintro>
    <xi:include href="developer/architecture.xml" />
    <xi:include href="developer/devQuickstart.xml" />
    <xi:include href="developer/externalConnectors.xml" />
    <xi:include href="developer/internalConnectors.xml" />
    <xi:include href="developer/features.xml"/>
    <xi:include href="developer/workflow.xml"/>
    <xi:include href="developer/context.xml"/>
    <xi:include href="developer/guidelines.xml" />
    <xi:include href="developer/wrapped.xml" />
  </part>

  <part id="domainsAndConnectors">
    <title>Domains and Connectors</title>
    <partintro>
      <para>
        This part summarizes and explains the usage of the available OpenEngSB domains and tool connectors.
      </para>
      <para>
        The target audience of this part are developers of OpenEngSB.
      </para>
    </partintro>
    <xi:include href="domains/domains.xml"/>
  </part>

  <part id="appendix">
    <title>Appendix</title>
    <xi:include href="appendix/documentation.xml" />
    <xi:include href="appendix/javastyle.xml" />
    <xi:include href="appendix/glossary.xml" />
    <xi:include href="appendix/license.xml" />
  </part>

</book>
